docs.abstract: The New York senator anchored her candidacy in issues of women’s equality, but she was unable to gain traction and her failure to qualify for the next debate convinced her to withdraw.
docs.snippet: The New York senator anchored her candidacy in issues of women’s equality, but she was unable to gain traction and her failure to qualify for the next debate convinced her to withdraw.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Kirsten Gillibrand of New York, who presented herself in the presidential race as a champion of women and families, said Wednesday that she was withdrawing from the Democratic primary after failing to qualify for a third debate next month — a development she described as fatal to her candidacy.

headline.main: Gillibrand Drops Out of 2020 Democratic Presidential Race
headline.print_headline: Gillibrand Ends Campaign After Missing Debate Threshold

docs.abstract: “There is no prize for someone who tries to hold accountable a powerful man who is good at his day job,” Ms. Gillibrand said after Mr. Franken spoke out about his resignation.
docs.snippet: “There is no prize for someone who tries to hold accountable a powerful man who is good at his day job,” Ms. Gillibrand said after Mr. Franken spoke out about his resignation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Chuck Schumer, the minority leader, and several Democratic senators running for president aligned themselves with Senator Kirsten Gillibrand on Tuesday, standing by their calls for Al Franken to resign from the Senate more than 18 months ago following numerous allegations of sexual misconduct.

headline.main: Al Franken Has Regrets. Kirsten Gillibrand Does Not.
headline.print_headline: He Regrets That He Quit, But She’s Not Sorry at All

byline.original: By Lisa Lerer and Shane Goldmacher

docs.abstract: He spent years focusing on his city’s economic record but it is his record on policing, once a footnote, that is overshadowing his presidential campaign.

docs.lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — On a Tuesday in March, just after Pete Buttigieg began to catch fire with Democrats nationally, he flew home for his final State of the City address.

headline.main: Pete Buttigieg Was Rising. Then Came South Bend’s Policing Crisis.
headline.print_headline: Police Crisis Tempers Buttigieg’s National Ascent

byline.original: By Trip Gabriel and Richard A. Oppel Jr

docs.abstract: Calling Mr. Trump ‘completely unfit,’ Mr. Walsh, a conservative radio host, will adopt a television-centric strategy to try to rattle a media-obsessed president.
docs.snippet: Calling Mr. Trump ‘completely unfit,’ Mr. Walsh, a conservative radio host, will adopt a television-centric strategy to try to rattle a media-obsessed president.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joe Walsh, the conservative radio show host and former Republican lawmaker from Illinois who rode the 2010 Tea Party wave to serve one term in Congress, announced on Sunday that he is running for president, challenging President Trump for the Republican nomination.

headline.main: Joe Walsh Confirms He Will Challenge Trump for Republican Nomination
headline.print_headline: Conservative Radio Host Says He Will Challenge Trump in G.O.P. Primary

docs.abstract: In an interview, Ms. Harris sought to paint her prosecutorial career as a reason voters should rely on her to deliver a criminal justice overhaul. But her critics say she has been part of the problem.
docs.snippet: In an interview, Ms. Harris sought to paint her prosecutorial career as a reason voters should rely on her to deliver a criminal justice overhaul. But her critics say she has been part of the problem.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California released a sweeping proposal on Monday to overhaul the criminal justice system, vowing to end mass incarceration and revamp police practices through a progressive wish list of policies, including some ideas Ms. Harris previously rejected during her years as a district attorney and state attorney general.

headline.main: ‘Trust Me’: Kamala Harris Makes Big Play on Criminal Justice Reform
headline.print_headline: Harris Says ‘Trust Me’ on Need for Criminal Justice Reform

docs.abstract: After a fatal shooting prompted scrutiny of his handling of police matters, the South Bend, Ind., mayor put forth new proposals to “dismantle racist structures and systems.’’

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Pete Buttigieg, whose presidential campaign is struggling to appeal to African-American voters even as it gains more support from Democratic donors, on Thursday released a plan to “dismantle racist structures and systems” in the federal government.

headline.main: Buttigieg, Struggling With Black Voters, Releases Plan to Address Racial Inequities
headline.print_headline: Buttigieg Releases Plan  To Fight Race Problems

byline.original: By Reid J. Epstein and Richard A. Oppel Jr

docs.abstract: A Buttigieg campaign memo that surfaced last week suggested “being gay was a barrier” to support from some black voters in South Carolina.

docs.lead_paragraph: ROCK HILL, S.C. — Addressing a conference of African-American church congregations in this vote-rich city, Pete Buttigieg quoted scripture on Sunday morning and extolled his “Douglass Plan” to combat racial inequities in America, one of several attempts this weekend to confront his strikingly low support among black voters.

headline.main: As Pete Buttigieg Courts Black Voters, His Sexuality Is a Hurdle for Some
headline.print_headline: As Buttigieg Courts Black Voters, His Sexuality Is a Hurdle

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts brought her ascendant presidential campaign to New York City on Monday night, unspooling a forceful argument for attacking corruption in government in a defining speech of her White House bid.
